Interface ExperimentType<S>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of the data describing the experiment state, including configuration and results
    All Superinterfaces:

    All Known Subinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChemicalMapExperimentType, SpectrumExperimentType

    public interface ExperimentType<S>
extends uk.co.strangeskies.reflection.Reified
    A type of experiment which may be available to be executed on a particular instrument.

      • mayComeBefore

        boolean mayComeBefore(ExperimentNode<?,?> penultimateDescendantNode,
                      ExperimentType<?> descendantNodeType)
        Test whether a node of the given type may follow from the given node and be validly added as its child. The penultimate descendant node should be a descendant of a node of this type.

        This test is performed on all ancestors when an attempt is made to add a new node.

        Parameters:
        penultimateDescendantNode - the candidate parent node
        descendantNodeType - the candidate child node
        Returns:
        true if a node of the given type may be added as a child of the given node, false otherwise
